            <h2>Introduction to Arrays</h2>
            <p>Arrays are a fundamental data structure used to store elements of the same type in a contiguous block of memory. They provide fast access to elements by index, making them ideal for various applications in programming.</p>
            
            <h2>Why Use Arrays?</h2>
            <p>Arrays offer several benefits, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Constant-time access to elements via indexing.</li>
                <li>Efficient iteration through elements.</li>
                <li>Simple implementation and use in many algorithms and applications.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Common Operations</h2>
            <p>Common operations on arrays include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Accessing elements by index.</li>
                <li>Updating elements at specific positions.</li>
                <li>Iterating through elements using loops.</li>
                <li>Sorting and searching elements.</li>
            </ul>
